Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createRegion(25.10)                                        createRegion(25.10)

Name
       createRegion - Creates a region for a module or a group

Syntax
        createRegion

       [-help]

       obj_name

       box

       [-floating]

       Creates  a  region  for a module or a group. Use this command after im-
       porting the design. To delete regions, use unplaceGuide.

Parameters
       box    Specifies the constraint box in<llx lly urx ury>:

              * llx: Specifies the lower left x coordinate of the region area.

              * lly: Specifies the lower left y coordinate of the region area.

              * urx: Specifies the upper right  x  coordinate  of  the  region
                area.

              * ury:  Specifies  the  upper  right  y coordinate of the region
                area.

              Data_type: box, required

       -floating
              Creates a floating region. The floating region/fence  constraint
              allows  the  entire region/fence to move as a cluster across the
              core area.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each createRegion parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createRegion

       <obj_name>
              Specifies the name of the module or the group.

              Data_type: string required

Example
       The following command creates a module guide in the floorplan view with
       status Region:

       createRegion DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST 433.0 793.88 1327.96 1287.8

       before placement (Floorplan view):

       After placement (Physical view):

